NAME
	signal-feed (display) - parse one whitespace-separated record per line from the file at the mount path and render a scrollable colour-coded list

INTERFACE
	display (MatrixDisplay)

READS
	.	the mount path itself is a FILE (e.g. /n/tbl4/signals):
		one signal per line, whitespace fields:
		id asset direction confidence signal_type timestamp

WRITES
	none (renders only)

DESCRIPTION
	Lines are reversed on load (source delivers newest-first) and
	rendered newest-last.  Direction colours each row (long/short)
	with a +/-/~ indicator; the timestamp renders as HH:MM sliced
	from an ISO timestamp.  Wheel scrolls one row; click or drag in
	the right gutter jumps the scrollbar proportionally.  The format
	is plain text lines, not JSON.

SEE ALSO
	alert-watcher (watches the same signals file)
